---
layout: default
title: Page Not Found
permalink: /404.html
---

<%# ── Top card ─────────────────────────────────────────────── %>
<div style="display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:2rem 1rem 1rem;">
  <div style="display:flex; align-items:stretch; max-width:56rem; width:100%; background:var(--bg-surface); border-radius:calc(var(--radius)*2); box-shadow:var(--shadow-md); overflow:hidden;">

    <div style="flex:0 0 42%; min-height:22rem; overflow:hidden;">
      <img src="<%= relative_url '/images/404.jpg' %>"
           alt="The Good Shepherd seeking a lost sheep"
           style="width:100%; height:100%; object-fit:cover; display:block;">
    </div>

    <div style="flex:1; padding:2.5rem 2.5rem 2.5rem 2rem; display:flex; flex-direction:column; justify-content:center;">
      <div style="display:inline-block; font-size:0.75rem; font-family:var(--font-sans); font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--purple-light); border:1.5px solid var(--purple-light); border-radius:2rem; padding:0.25rem 0.85rem; margin-bottom:1rem; width:fit-content;">
        404 — Page Not Found
      </div>
      <h1 style="font-size:1.75rem; margin:0 0 0.75rem; line-height:1.25;">
        Do you sometimes feel like a lost sheep?
      </h1>
      <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin:0 0 1.25rem; line-height:1.7;">
        Wandering aimlessly, unsure of where you belong — Jesus is looking for you.
        He is the Good Shepherd. Trust in Him to bring you home where you belong.
      </p>
      <blockquote style="border-left:3px solid var(--gold); padding-left:1rem; margin:0 0 1.75rem; font-style:italic; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        "For the Son of Man came to seek and to save the lost."
        <cite style="display:block; margin-top:0.35rem; font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; color:var(--gold);">— Luke 19:10 (ESV)</cite>
      </blockquote>
      <a href="<%= relative_url '/' %>" style="display:inline-block; background:var(--purple-mid); color:#fff; font-weight:700; font-family:var(--font-sans); text-decoration:none; padding:0.65rem 1.75rem; border-radius:var(--radius); width:fit-content;">
        Return to Home
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<%# ── Romans Road ─────────────────────────────────────────── %>
<div style="max-width:56rem; margin:0 auto; padding:1rem 1rem 3rem;">

  <h2 style="text-align:center; font-size:1.4rem; margin:2rem 0 0.5rem; color:var(--purple-light); letter-spacing:0.03em;">
    The Path Home
  </h2>
  <p style="text-align:center; color:var(--text-muted); font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; margin:0 0 2rem;">
    The Bible calls this feeling of being lost what it truly is — and shows the way back.
  </p>

  <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:1.25rem;">

    <div style="background:var(--bg-surface); border-radius:var(--radius); box-shadow:var(--shadow-sm); padding:1.5rem 1.75rem; border-left:4px solid var(--purple-mid);">
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.75rem; line-height:1.7; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        We don't wander by accident. Scripture is clear that every one of us has turned away from God.
      </p>
      <blockquote style="margin:0; padding-left:1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--gold); font-style:italic; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        "For all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God."
        <cite style="display:block; margin-top:0.3rem; font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; color:var(--gold);">— Romans 3:23 (ESV)</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div style="background:var(--bg-surface); border-radius:var(--radius); box-shadow:var(--shadow-sm); padding:1.5rem 1.75rem; border-left:4px solid var(--purple-mid);">
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.75rem; line-height:1.7; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        Sin carries a consequence — but God refuses to leave the story there.
      </p>
      <blockquote style="margin:0; padding-left:1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--gold); font-style:italic; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        "For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord."
        <cite style="display:block; margin-top:0.3rem; font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; color:var(--gold);">— Romans 6:23 (ESV)</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div style="background:var(--bg-surface); border-radius:var(--radius); box-shadow:var(--shadow-sm); padding:1.5rem 1.75rem; border-left:4px solid var(--purple-mid);">
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.75rem; line-height:1.7; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        The Good Shepherd didn't wait for you to find your way back. He came looking — at great cost.
      </p>
      <blockquote style="margin:0; padding-left:1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--gold); font-style:italic; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        "But God shows his love for us in that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us."
        <cite style="display:block; margin-top:0.3rem; font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; color:var(--gold);">— Romans 5:8 (ESV)</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div style="background:var(--bg-surface); border-radius:var(--radius); box-shadow:var(--shadow-sm); padding:1.5rem 1.75rem; border-left:4px solid var(--purple-mid);">
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.75rem; line-height:1.7; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        Coming home is simpler than you may think. It begins with a confession and a trust.
      </p>
      <blockquote style="margin:0; padding-left:1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--gold); font-style:italic; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        "If you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved."
        <cite style="display:block; margin-top:0.3rem; font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; color:var(--gold);">— Romans 10:9 (ESV)</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div style="background:var(--bg-surface); border-radius:var(--radius); box-shadow:var(--shadow-sm); padding:1.5rem 1.75rem; border-left:4px solid var(--gold);">
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.75rem; line-height:1.7; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        And the promise is for everyone — no exceptions, no fine print.
      </p>
      <blockquote style="margin:0; padding-left:1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--gold); font-style:italic; color:var(--text-secondary);">
        "For everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved."
        <cite style="display:block; margin-top:0.3rem; font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; color:var(--gold);">— Romans 10:13 (ESV)</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div style="background:var(--purple-deep); border-radius:var(--radius); box-shadow:var(--shadow-md); padding:1.75rem 1.75rem; border-left:4px solid var(--gold);">
      <p style="margin:0 0 0.75rem; line-height:1.7; color:#fff; opacity:0.9;">
        This is the heart of it all — the reason the Shepherd left the ninety-nine to find you.
      </p>
      <blockquote style="margin:0; padding-left:1rem; border-left:3px solid var(--gold); font-style:italic; color:#fff; opacity:0.9;">
        "For God so loved the world, that he gave his only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life. For God did not send his Son into the world to condemn the world, but in order that the world might be saved through him."
        <cite style="display:block; margin-top:0.35rem; font-size:0.85rem; font-style:normal; color:var(--gold);">— John 3:16–17 (ESV)</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>

  </div>

</div>
